Manchester United midfielder, Bruno Fernandes, has won the club’s Goal of the 2020/21 Season. Fernandes won the prize for his astonishing effort against Everton during the exciting 3-3 draw at Old Trafford in February this year. The Portugal international beat the likes of Paul Pogba and Edinson Cavani to win the prize. Man United made the announcement in a post via their website on Tuesday ahead of their Premier League clash with Fulham. Fernandes has so far scored 28 goals for Man United this season, which is a record for a Premier League midfielder in a single campaign across all competitions, beating Chelsea legend Frank Lampard’s mark of 27 set in 2010. The 26-year-old joined Manchester United from Sporting in January 2020. EPL: I want to be Man Utd manager – Bruno Fernandes 